This paper is about a natural language generation system for spoken dialogue systems, which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The system is based on recurrent neural networks and the sequence-to-sequence approach, which are commonly used in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the evaluation of the system using automatic metrics and a human pairwise preference test, which could be relevant to the sub-categories of software engineering (cs.SD) and human-computer interaction (cs.HC).
